26// half
27// slot Frame
28// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
29// n+3 | parameter n |
30// ... | ... |
31// 4 | parameter 1 | or parameter 2
32// 3 | parameter 0 | or parameter 1
33// 2 | (result address) | or parameter 0
34// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
35// 1 | return addr (lr) |
36// 0 | previous frame (fp)|
37// -----+--------------------+ <-- frame ptr (fp)
38// -1 | StackFrame::WASM |
39// -2 | instance |
40// -3 | feedback vector |
41// -4 | tiering budget |
42// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
43// -5 | slot 0 (high) | ^
44// -6 | slot 0 (low) | |
45// -7 | slot 1 (high) | Frame slots
46// -8 | slot 1 (low) | |
47// | | v
48// -----+--------------------+ <-- stack ptr (sp)
49//
50static_assert(2 * kSystemPointerSize == LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize,
51 "Slot size should be twice the size of the 32 bit pointer.");
52// kPatchInstructionsRequired sets a maximum limit of how many instructions that
53// PatchPrepareStackFrame will use in order to increase the stack appropriately.
54// Three instructions are required to sub a large constant, movw + movt + sub.
55constexpr int32_t kPatchInstructionsRequired = 3;
56constexpr int kHalfStackSlotSize = LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize >> 1;
57
58inline MemOperand GetStackSlot(int offset) { return MemOperand(fp, -offset); }
59
60inline MemOperand GetHalfStackSlot(int offset, RegPairHalf half) {
61 int32_t half_offset =
62 half == kLowWord ? 0 : LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize / 2;
63 return MemOperand(offset > 0 ? fp : sp, -offset + half_offset);
64}

66inline MemOperand GetInstanceDataOperand() {
67 return GetStackSlot(WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kInstanceDataOffset);

70inline MemOperand GetMemOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
71 UseScratchRegisterScope* temps, Register addr,
72 Register offset, int32_t offset_imm,
73 unsigned shift_amount = 0) {
74 if (offset != no_reg) {
75 if (offset_imm == 0) return MemOperand(addr, offset, LSL, shift_amount);
76 Register tmp = temps->Acquire();
77 if (shift_amount == 0) {
78 assm->add(tmp, offset, Operand(offset_imm));
79 } else {
80 assm->lsl(tmp, offset, Operand(shift_amount));
81 assm->add(tmp, tmp, Operand(offset_imm));
82 }
83 return MemOperand(addr, tmp);
84 }
85 return MemOperand(addr, offset_imm);
86}
87
88inline Register CalculateActualAddress(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
89 UseScratchRegisterScope* temps,
90 Register addr_reg, Register offset_reg,
91 uintptr_t offset_imm,
92 Register result_reg = no_reg) {
93 if (offset_reg == no_reg && offset_imm == 0) {
94 if (result_reg == addr_reg || result_reg == no_reg) return addr_reg;
95 assm->mov(result_reg, addr_reg);
96 return result_reg;
97 }
98 if (result_reg == no_reg) result_reg = temps->Acquire();
99 if (offset_reg == no_reg) {
100 assm->add(result_reg, addr_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
101 } else {
102 assm->add(result_reg, addr_reg, Operand(offset_reg));
103 if (offset_imm != 0) assm->add(result_reg, result_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
104 }
105 return result_reg;
106}

108inline Condition MakeUnsigned(Condition cond) {
109 switch (cond) {
110 case kLessThan:
111 return kUnsignedLessThan;
112 case kLessThanEqual:
113 return kUnsignedLessThanEqual;
114 case kGreaterThan:
115 return kUnsignedGreaterThan;
116 case kGreaterThanEqual:
117 return kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual;
118 case kEqual:
119 case kNotEqual:
120 case kUnsignedLessThan:
121 case kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
122 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
123 case kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
124 return cond;
125 default:
126 UNREACHABLE();
127 }
128}

130template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, Register, Register, SBit, Condition),
131 void (Assembler::*op_with_carry)(Register, Register, const Operand&,
132 SBit, Condition)>
133inline void I64Binop(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
134 LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs) {
135 Register dst_low = dst.low_gp();
136 if (dst_low == lhs.high_gp() || dst_low == rhs.high_gp()) {
137 dst_low =
138 assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs, dst.high_gp()})
139 .gp();
140 }
141 (assm->*op)(dst_low, lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp(), SetCC, al);
142 (assm->*op_with_carry)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), Operand(rhs.high_gp()),
143 LeaveCC, al);
144 if (dst_low != dst.low_gp()) assm->mov(dst.low_gp(), dst_low);
145}
146
147template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, Register, const Operand&, SBit,
148 Condition),
149 void (Assembler::*op_with_carry)(Register, Register, const Operand&,
150 SBit, Condition)>
151inline void I64BinopI(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
152 LiftoffRegister lhs, int64_t imm) {
153 // The compiler allocated registers such that either {dst == lhs} or there is
154 // no overlap between the two.
155 DCHECK_NE(dst.low_gp(), lhs.high_gp());
156 int32_t imm_low_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm);
157 int32_t imm_high_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm >> 32);
158 (assm->*op)(dst.low_gp(), lhs.low_gp(), Operand(imm_low_word), SetCC, al);
159 (assm->*op_with_carry)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), Operand(imm_high_word),
160 LeaveCC, al);
161}

163template <void (MacroAssembler::*op)(Register, Register, Register, Register,
164 Register),
165 bool is_left_shift>
166inline void I64Shiftop(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
167 LiftoffRegister src, Register amount) {
168 Register src_low = src.low_gp();
169 Register src_high = src.high_gp();
170 Register dst_low = dst.low_gp();
171 Register dst_high = dst.high_gp();
172 // Left shift writes {dst_high} then {dst_low}, right shifts write {dst_low}
173 // then {dst_high}.
174 Register clobbered_dst_reg = is_left_shift ? dst_high : dst_low;
175 LiftoffRegList pinned{clobbered_dst_reg, src};
176 Register amount_capped =
177 pinned.set(assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
178 assm->and_(amount_capped, amount, Operand(0x3F));
179
180 // Ensure that writing the first half of {dst} does not overwrite the still
181 // needed half of {src}.
182 Register* later_src_reg = is_left_shift ? &src_low : &src_high;
183 if (*later_src_reg == clobbered_dst_reg) {
184 *later_src_reg = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
185 assm->MacroAssembler::Move(*later_src_reg, clobbered_dst_reg);
186 }
187
188 (assm->*op)(dst_low, dst_high, src_low, src_high, amount_capped);
189}

204enum class MinOrMax : uint8_t { kMin, kMax };
205template <typename RegisterType>
206inline void EmitFloatMinOrMax(LiftoffAssembler* assm, RegisterType dst,
207 RegisterType lhs, RegisterType rhs,
208 MinOrMax min_or_max) {
209 DCHECK(RegisterType::kSizeInBytes == 4 || RegisterType::kSizeInBytes == 8);
210 if (lhs == rhs) {
211 assm->MacroAssembler::Move(dst, lhs);
212 return;
213 }
214 Label done, is_nan;
215 if (min_or_max == MinOrMax::kMin) {
216 assm->MacroAssembler::FloatMin(dst, lhs, rhs, &is_nan);
217 } else {
218 assm->MacroAssembler::FloatMax(dst, lhs, rhs, &is_nan);
219 }
220 assm->b(&done);
221 assm->bind(&is_nan);
222 // Create a NaN output.
223 assm->vadd(dst, lhs, rhs);
224 assm->bind(&done);
225}
226
227inline Register EnsureNoAlias(Assembler* assm, Register reg,
228 Register must_not_alias,
229 UseScratchRegisterScope* temps) {
230 if (reg != must_not_alias) return reg;
231 Register tmp = temps->Acquire();
232 DCHECK_NE(reg, tmp);
233 assm->mov(tmp, reg);
234 return tmp;
235}

237inline void S128NarrowOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, NeonDataType dt,
238 NeonDataType sdt, LiftoffRegister dst,
239 LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs) {
240 if (dst == lhs) {
241 assm->vqmovn(dt, sdt, dst.low_fp(), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
242 assm->vqmovn(dt, sdt, dst.high_fp(), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs));
243 } else {
244 assm->vqmovn(dt, sdt, dst.high_fp(), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs));
245 assm->vqmovn(dt, sdt, dst.low_fp(), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
246 }
247}

249inline void F64x2Compare(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
250 LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs,
251 Condition cond) {
252 DCHECK(cond == eq || cond == ne || cond == lt || cond == le);
253
254 QwNeonRegister dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
255 QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
256 QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
257 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
258 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
259
260 assm->mov(scratch, Operand(0));
261 assm->VFPCompareAndSetFlags(left.low(), right.low());
262 assm->mov(scratch, Operand(-1), LeaveCC, cond);
263 if (cond == lt || cond == le) {
264 // Check for NaN.
265 assm->mov(scratch, Operand(0), LeaveCC, vs);
266 }
267 assm->vmov(dest.low(), scratch, scratch);
268
269 assm->mov(scratch, Operand(0));
270 assm->VFPCompareAndSetFlags(left.high(), right.high());
271 assm->mov(scratch, Operand(-1), LeaveCC, cond);
272 if (cond == lt || cond == le) {
273 // Check for NaN.
274 assm->mov(scratch, Operand(0), LeaveCC, vs);
275 }
276 assm->vmov(dest.high(), scratch, scratch);
277}
278
279inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister src, MemOperand dst,
280 ValueKind kind) {
281#ifdef DEBUG
282 // The {str} instruction needs a temp register when the immediate in the
283 // provided MemOperand does not fit into 12 bits. This happens for large stack
284 // frames. This DCHECK checks that the temp register is available when needed.
285 DCHECK(UseScratchRegisterScope{assm}.CanAcquire());
286#endif
287 switch (kind) {
288 case kI16:
289 assm->strh(src.gp(), dst);
290 break;
291 case kI32:
292 case kRefNull:
293 case kRef:
294 case kRtt:
295 assm->str(src.gp(), dst);
296 break;
297 case kI64:
298 // Positive offsets should be lowered to kI32.
299 assm->str(src.low_gp(), MemOperand(dst.rn(), dst.offset()));
300 assm->str(
301 src.high_gp(),
302 MemOperand(dst.rn(), dst.offset() + liftoff::kHalfStackSlotSize));
303 break;
304 case kF32:
305 assm->vstr(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()), dst);
306 break;
307 case kF64:
308 assm->vstr(src.fp(), dst);
309 break;
310 case kS128: {
311 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
312 Register addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(assm, &temps, dst.rn(),
313 no_reg, dst.offset());
314 assm->vst1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(src.low_fp(), 2), NeonMemOperand(addr));
315 break;
316 }
317 default:
318 UNREACHABLE();
319 }
320}
321
322inline void Load(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, MemOperand src,
323 ValueKind kind) {
324 switch (kind) {
325 case kI16:
326 assm->ldrh(dst.gp(), src);
327 break;
328 case kI32:
329 case kRefNull:
330 case kRef:
331 case kRtt:
332 assm->ldr(dst.gp(), src);
333 break;
334 case kI64:
335 assm->ldr(dst.low_gp(), MemOperand(src.rn(), src.offset()));
336 assm->ldr(
337 dst.high_gp(),
338 MemOperand(src.rn(), src.offset() + liftoff::kHalfStackSlotSize));
339 break;
340 case kF32:
341 assm->vldr(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src);
342 break;
343 case kF64:
344 assm->vldr(dst.fp(), src);
345 break;
346 case kS128: {
347 // Get memory address of slot to fill from.
348 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
349 Register addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(assm, &temps, src.rn(),
350 no_reg, src.offset());
351 assm->vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp(), 2), NeonMemOperand(addr));
352 break;
353 }
354 default:
355 UNREACHABLE();
356 }
357}

359constexpr int MaskFromNeonDataType(NeonDataType dt) {
360 switch (dt) {
361 case NeonS8:
362 case NeonU8:
363 return 7;
364 case NeonS16:
365 case NeonU16:
366 return 15;
367 case NeonS32:
368 case NeonU32:
369 return 31;
370 case NeonS64:
371 case NeonU64:
372 return 63;
373 default:
374 UNREACHABLE();
375 return 0;
376 }
377}
378
379enum ShiftDirection { kLeft, kRight };
380
381template <ShiftDirection dir = kLeft, NeonDataType dt, NeonSize sz>
382inline void EmitSimdShift(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
383 LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs) {
384 constexpr int mask = MaskFromNeonDataType(dt);
385 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
386 QwNeonRegister tmp = temps.AcquireQ();
387 Register shift = temps.Acquire();
388 assm->and_(shift, rhs.gp(), Operand(mask));
389 assm->vdup(sz, tmp, shift);
390 if (dir == kRight) {
391 assm->vneg(sz, tmp, tmp);
392 }
393 assm->vshl(dt, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
394 liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs), tmp);
395}
396
397template <ShiftDirection dir, NeonDataType dt>
398inline void EmitSimdShiftImmediate(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
399 LiftoffRegister lhs, int32_t rhs) {
400 // vshr by 0 is not allowed, so check for it, and only move if dst != lhs.
401 int32_t shift = rhs & MaskFromNeonDataType(dt);
402 if (shift) {
403 if (dir == kLeft) {
404 assm->vshl(dt, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
405 liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs), shift);
406 } else {
407 assm->vshr(dt, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
408 liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs), shift);
409 }
410 } else if (dst != lhs) {
411 assm->vmov(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
412 liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
413 }
414}
415
416inline void EmitAnyTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
417 LiftoffRegister src) {
418 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
419 DwVfpRegister scratch = temps.AcquireD();
420 assm->vpmax(NeonU32, scratch, src.low_fp(), src.high_fp());
421 assm->vpmax(NeonU32, scratch, scratch, scratch);
422 assm->ExtractLane(dst.gp(), scratch, NeonS32, 0);
423 assm->cmp(dst.gp(), Operand(0));
424 assm->mov(dst.gp(), Operand(1), LeaveCC, ne);
425}

427class CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters {
428 public:
429 explicit CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
430 LiftoffRegList pinned = {})
431 : assm_(assm), pinned_(pinned) {}
432
433 ~CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters() {
434 for (Register reg : must_pop_) {
435 assm_->Pop(reg);
436 }
437 }
438
439 Register Acquire() {
440 if (assm_->cache_state()->has_unused_register(kGpReg, pinned_)) {
441 return pinned_.set(
442 assm_->cache_state()->unused_register(kGpReg, pinned_).gp());
443 }
444
445 RegList available =
446 kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs - pinned_.GetGpList() - must_pop_;
447 DCHECK(!available.is_empty());
448 // Use {last()} here so we can just iterate forwards in the destructor.
449 Register reg = available.last();
450 assm_->Push(reg);
451 must_pop_.set(reg);
452 return reg;
453 }
454
455 private:
456 LiftoffAssembler* const assm_;
457 LiftoffRegList pinned_;
458 RegList must_pop_;
459};

463int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
464 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ARMv7)) {
465 bailout(kUnsupportedArchitecture, "Liftoff needs ARMv7");
466 return 0;
467 }
468 uint32_t offset = static_cast<uint32_t>(pc_offset());
469 // PatchPrepareStackFrame will patch this in order to increase the stack
470 // appropriately. Additional nops are required as the bytes operand might
471 // require extra moves to encode.
472 for (int i = 0; i < liftoff::kPatchInstructionsRequired; i++) {
473 nop();
474 }
475 DCHECK_EQ(offset + liftoff::kPatchInstructionsRequired * kInstrSize,
476 pc_offset());
477 return offset;
478}
479
480void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
481// The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
482// `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
483#ifdef __clang__
484 static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
485 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
486 kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
487 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
488#endif
489
490 // On ARM, we must push at least {lr} before calling the stub, otherwise
491 // it would get clobbered with no possibility to recover it.
492 Register scratch = r7;
493 mov(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM)));
494 PushCommonFrame(scratch);
495 LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
496 WasmValue(declared_function_index));
497 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
498}
499
500void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
501 int stack_param_delta) {
502 {
503 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
504 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
505
506 // Push the return address and frame pointer to complete the stack frame.
507 sub(sp, sp, Operand(8));
508 ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 4));
509 str(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
510 ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 0));
511 str(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
512
513 // Shift the whole frame upwards.
514 int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params + 2;
515 for (int i = slot_count - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
516 ldr(scratch, MemOperand(sp, i * 4));
517 str(scratch, MemOperand(fp, (i - stack_param_delta) * 4));
518 }
519 }
520
521 // Set the new stack and frame pointer.
522 sub(sp, fp, Operand(stack_param_delta * 4));
523 Pop(lr, fp);
524}

526void LiftoffAssembler::AlignFrameSize() {}
527
528void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
529 int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
530 bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
531 // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
532 // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
533 // for them anymore.
534 int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
535 // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector.
536 if (feedback_vector_slot) {
537 frame_size -= kSystemPointerSize;
538 }
539
540 PatchingAssembler patching_assembler(AssemblerOptions{},
541 buffer_start_ + offset,
542 liftoff::kPatchInstructionsRequired);
543 if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
544 // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
545 // done with it.
546 patching_assembler.sub(sp, sp, Operand(frame_size));
547 patching_assembler.PadWithNops();
548 return;
549 }
550
551 // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
552 // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
553 // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
554 // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
555 // replace the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} with a jump to OOL code that does
556 // this "extended stack check".
557 //
558 // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
559 // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
560 // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
561 // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
562 // large frame.
563
564 // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
565 // {pc_offset()}).
566 patching_assembler.b(pc_offset() - offset - Instruction::kPcLoadDelta);
567 patching_assembler.PadWithNops();
568
569 // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
570 // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
571 // check in the condition code.
572 RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
573 Label continuation;
574 if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
575 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
576 Register stack_limit = temps.Acquire();
577 LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
578 add(stack_limit, stack_limit, Operand(frame_size));
579 cmp(sp, stack_limit);
580 b(cs /* higher or same */, &continuation);
581 }
582
583 if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
584 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
585 regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
586 regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
587 for (auto reg : kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
588 for (auto reg : kFpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
589 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
590 mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(), Operand(frame_size));
591 add(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), fp,
592 Operand(stack_param_slots * kStackSlotSize +
593 CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp));
594 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
595 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
596 } else {
597 Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
598 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
599 // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
600 safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
601 if (v8_flags.debug_code) stop();
602 }
603
604 bind(&continuation);
605
606 // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
607 // decrementing the SP; consult {MacroAssembler::AllocateStackSpace}.
608 AllocateStackSpace(frame_size);
609
610 // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
611 // right after the reserved space for the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} (which
612 // is a branch now).
613 int func_start_offset =
614 offset + liftoff::kPatchInstructionsRequired * kInstrSize;
615 b(func_start_offset - pc_offset() - Instruction::kPcLoadDelta);
616}
617
618void LiftoffAssembler::FinishCode() { CheckConstPool(true, false); }
619
620void LiftoffAssembler::AbortCompilation() { AbortedCodeGeneration(); }

624 return WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kFeedbackVectorOffset;
625}

627int LiftoffAssembler::SlotSizeForType(ValueKind kind) {
628 switch (kind) {
629 case kS128:
630 return value_kind_size(kind);
631 default:
632 return kStackSlotSize;
633 }
634}

636bool LiftoffAssembler::NeedsAlignment(ValueKind kind) {
637 return kind == kS128 || is_reference(kind);
638}
639
640void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
641 Label* ool_label,
642 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
643 {
644 liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters temps{this};
645 Register budget_array = temps.Acquire();
646
647 Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
648 if (instance_data == no_reg) {
649 instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the temp register.
650 LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
651 }
652
653 constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
654 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
655 ldr(budget_array, MemOperand{instance_data, kArrayOffset});
656
657 int budget_arr_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
658 // If the offset cannot be used in the operand directly, add it once to the
659 // budget array to avoid doing this multiple times below.
660 if (!ImmediateFitsAddrMode2Instruction(budget_arr_offset)) {
661 add(budget_array, budget_array, Operand{budget_arr_offset});
662 budget_arr_offset = 0;
663 }
664
665 Register budget = temps.Acquire();
666 MemOperand budget_addr{budget_array, budget_arr_offset};
667 ldr(budget, budget_addr);
668 sub(budget, budget, Operand{budget_used}, SetCC);
669 str(budget, budget_addr);
670 }
671 b(ool_label, mi);
672}
673
674Register LiftoffAssembler::LoadOldFramePointer() {
675 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
676 return fp;
677 }
678 LiftoffRegister old_fp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {});
679 Label done, call_runtime;
680 ldr(old_fp.gp(), MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
681 cmp(old_fp.gp(),
682 Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
683 b(&call_runtime, eq);
684 mov(old_fp.gp(), fp);
685 jmp(&done);
686
687 bind(&call_runtime);
688 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = cache_state()->used_registers;
689 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
690 MacroAssembler::Move(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
691 PrepareCallCFunction(1);
692 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_load_old_fp(), 1);
693 if (old_fp.gp() != kReturnRegister0) {
694 mov(old_fp.gp(), kReturnRegister0);
695 }
696 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
697
698 bind(&done);
699 return old_fp.gp();
700}
701
702void LiftoffAssembler::CheckStackShrink() {
703 {
704 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
705 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
706 ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
707 cmp(scratch,
708 Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
709 }
710 Label done;
711 b(&done, ne);
712 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
713 for (auto reg : kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
714 for (auto reg : kFpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
715 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
716 MacroAssembler::Move(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
717 PrepareCallCFunction(1);
718 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
719 // Restore old FP. We don't need to restore old SP explicitly, because
720 // it will be restored from FP in LeaveFrame before return.
721 mov(fp, kReturnRegister0);
722 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
723 bind(&done);
724}
725
726void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
727 switch (value.type().kind()) {
728 case kI32:
729 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.gp(), Operand(value.to_i32()));
730 break;
731 case kI64: {
732 int32_t low_word = value.to_i64();
733 int32_t high_word = value.to_i64() >> 32;
734 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.low_gp(), Operand(low_word));
735 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.high_gp(), Operand(high_word));
736 break;
737 }
738 case kF32:
739 vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(reg.fp()), value.to_f32_boxed());
740 break;
741 case kF64: {
742 Register extra_scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
743 vmov(reg.fp(), base::Double(value.to_f64_boxed().get_bits()),
744 extra_scratch);
745 break;
746 }
747 default:
748 UNREACHABLE();
749 }
750}

753 ldr(dst, liftoff::GetInstanceDataOperand());
754}

759 static_assert(!COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
760 ldr(dst, MemOperand{src_addr, offset});
761}

763void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFromInstance(Register dst, Register instance,
764 int offset, int size) {
765 DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
766 MemOperand src{instance, offset};
767 switch (size) {
768 case 1:
769 ldrb(dst, src);
770 break;
771 case 4:
772 ldr(dst, src);
773 break;
774 default:
775 UNIMPLEMENTED();
776 }
777}

792namespace liftoff {
793#define __ lasm->
794inline void LoadInternal(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, LiftoffRegister dst,
795 Register src_addr, Register offset_reg,
796 int32_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
797 uint32_t* protected_load_pc = nullptr,
798 bool needs_shift = false) {
799 unsigned shift_amount = needs_shift ? type.size_log_2() : 0;
800 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type.value_type() == kWasmI64, dst.is_gp_pair());
801 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
802 if (type.value() == LoadType::kF64Load ||
803 type.value() == LoadType::kF32Load ||
804 type.value() == LoadType::kS128Load) {
805 // Remove the DCHECK and implement scaled offsets for these types if needed.
806 // For now this path is never used.
807 DCHECK(!needs_shift);
808 Register actual_src_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
809 lasm, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
810 if (type.value() == LoadType::kF64Load) {
811 // Armv6 is not supported so Neon can be used to avoid alignment issues.
812 CpuFeatureScope scope(lasm, NEON);
813 __ vld1(Neon64, NeonListOperand(dst.fp()),
814 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
815 } else if (type.value() == LoadType::kF32Load) {
816 // TODO(arm): Use vld1 for f32 when implemented in simulator as used for
817 // f64. It supports unaligned access.
818 Register scratch =
819 (actual_src_addr == src_addr) ? temps.Acquire() : actual_src_addr;
820 __ ldr(scratch, MemOperand(actual_src_addr));
821 __ vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), scratch);
822 } else {
823 // Armv6 is not supported so Neon can be used to avoid alignment issues.
824 CpuFeatureScope scope(lasm, NEON);
825 __ vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp(), 2),
826 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
827 }
828 } else {
829 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(lasm, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg,
830 offset_imm, shift_amount);
831 if (protected_load_pc) *protected_load_pc = __ pc_offset();
832 switch (type.value()) {
833 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
834 __ ldrb(dst.gp(), src_op);
835 break;
836 case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
837 __ ldrb(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
838 __ mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
839 break;
840 case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
841 __ ldrsb(dst.gp(), src_op);
842 break;
843 case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
844 __ ldrsb(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
845 __ asr(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(31));
846 break;
847 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
848 __ ldrh(dst.gp(), src_op);
849 break;
850 case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
851 __ ldrh(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
852 __ mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
853 break;
854 case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
855 __ ldrsh(dst.gp(), src_op);
856 break;
857 case LoadType::kI32Load:
858 __ ldr(dst.gp(), src_op);
859 break;
860 case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
861 __ ldrsh(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
862 __ asr(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(31));
863 break;
864 case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
865 __ ldr(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
866 __ mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
867 break;
868 case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
869 __ ldr(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
870 __ asr(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(31));
871 break;
872 case LoadType::kI64Load:
873 __ ldr(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
874 // GetMemOp may use a scratch register as the offset register, in which
875 // case, calling GetMemOp again will fail due to the assembler having
876 // ran out of scratch registers.
877 if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
878 src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(lasm, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg,
879 offset_imm + kSystemPointerSize);
880 } else {
881 __ add(src_op.rm(), src_op.rm(), Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
882 }
883 __ ldr(dst.high_gp(), src_op);
884 break;
885 default:
886 UNREACHABLE();
887 }
888 }
889}
890#undef __
891} // namespace liftoff

898 static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt32Size);

900 offset_imm, LoadType::kI32Load, protected_load_pc,
901 needs_shift);
902}

907 LoadTaggedPointer(dst, src_addr, no_reg, offset);

909
910void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFullPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
911 int32_t offset_imm) {
912 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
913 MemOperand src_op =
914 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, no_reg, offset_imm);
915 ldr(dst, src_op);
916}
917
918void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
919 Register offset_reg,
920 int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
921 LiftoffRegList pinned,
922 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
923 SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
924 static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt32Size);
925 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
926 Register actual_offset_reg = offset_reg;
927 if (offset_reg != no_reg && offset_imm != 0) {
928 if (cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(offset_reg))) {
929 // The code below only needs a scratch register if the {MemOperand} given
930 // to {str} has an offset outside the uint12 range. After doing the
931 // addition below we will not pass an immediate offset to {str} though, so
932 // we can use the scratch register here.
933 actual_offset_reg = temps.Acquire();
934 }
935 add(actual_offset_reg, offset_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
936 }
937 MemOperand dst_op = actual_offset_reg == no_reg
938 ? MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_imm)
939 : MemOperand(dst_addr, actual_offset_reg);
940
941 if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
942
943 str(src, dst_op);
944
945 if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
946
947 // The write barrier.
948 Label exit;
949 CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
950 kZero, &exit);
951 JumpIfSmi(src, &exit);
952 CheckPageFlag(src, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &exit);
953 CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(
954 dst_addr,
955 actual_offset_reg == no_reg ? Operand(offset_imm)
956 : Operand(actual_offset_reg),
957 SaveFPRegsMode::kSave, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
958 bind(&exit);
959}
960
961void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
962 Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
963 LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
964 bool /* is_load_mem */, bool /* i64_offset */,
965 bool needs_shift) {
966 // Offsets >=2GB are statically OOB on 32-bit systems.
967 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
968 liftoff::LoadInternal(this, dst, src_addr, offset_reg,
969 static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm), type,
970 protected_load_pc, needs_shift);
971}
972
973void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
974 uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
975 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
976 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
977 bool /* is_store_mem */, bool /* i64_offset */) {
978 // Offsets >=2GB are statically OOB on 32-bit systems.
979 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
980 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
981 if (type.value() == StoreType::kF64Store) {
982 Register actual_dst_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
983 this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
984 // Armv6 is not supported so Neon can be used to avoid alignment issues.
985 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, NEON);
986 vst1(Neon64, NeonListOperand(src.fp()), NeonMemOperand(actual_dst_addr));
987 } else if (type.value() == StoreType::kS128Store) {
988 Register actual_dst_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
989 this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
990 // Armv6 is not supported so Neon can be used to avoid alignment issues.
991 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, NEON);
992 vst1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(src.low_fp(), 2),
993 NeonMemOperand(actual_dst_addr));
994 } else if (type.value() == StoreType::kF32Store) {
995 // TODO(arm): Use vst1 for f32 when implemented in simulator as used for
996 // f64. It supports unaligned access.
997 Register actual_dst_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
998 this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
999 liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters liftoff_temps{this, pinned};
1000 Register scratch =
1001 temps.CanAcquire() ? temps.Acquire() : liftoff_temps.Acquire();
1002 vmov(scratch, liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()));
1003 str(scratch, MemOperand(actual_dst_addr));
1004 } else {
1005 MemOperand dst_op =
1006 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1007 if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
1008 switch (type.value()) {
1009 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1010 src = src.low();
1011 [[fallthrough]];
1012 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1013 strb(src.gp(), dst_op);
1014 break;
1015 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1016 src = src.low();
1017 [[fallthrough]];
1018 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1019 strh(src.gp(), dst_op);
1020 break;
1021 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1022 src = src.low();
1023 [[fallthrough]];
1024 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1025 str(src.gp(), dst_op);
1026 break;
1027 case StoreType::kI64Store:
1028 str(src.low_gp(), dst_op);
1029 // GetMemOp may use a scratch register as the offset register, in which
1030 // case, calling GetMemOp again will fail due to the assembler having
1031 // ran out of scratch registers.
1032 if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
1033 dst_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg,
1034 offset_imm + kSystemPointerSize);
1035 } else {
1036 add(dst_op.rm(), dst_op.rm(), Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
1037 }
1038 str(src.high_gp(), dst_op);
1039 break;
1040 default:
1041 UNREACHABLE();
1042 }
1043 }
1044}

1046namespace liftoff {
1047#define __ lasm->
1048
1049inline void AtomicOp32(
1050 LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
1051 uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result,
1052 LiftoffRegList pinned,
1053 void (Assembler::*load)(Register, Register, Condition),
1054 void (Assembler::*store)(Register, Register, Register, Condition),
1055 void (*op)(LiftoffAssembler*, Register, Register, Register)) {
1056 Register store_result = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1057
1058 // Allocate an additional {temp} register to hold the result that should be
1059 // stored to memory. Note that {temp} and {store_result} are not allowed to be
1060 // the same register.
1061 Register temp = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1062
1063 // {LiftoffCompiler::AtomicBinop} ensures that {result} is unique.
1064 DCHECK(result.gp() != value.gp() && result.gp() != dst_addr &&
1065 result.gp() != offset_reg);
1066
1067 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
1068 Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1069 lasm, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1070
1071 __ dmb(ISH);
1072 Label retry;
1073 __ bind(&retry);
1074 (lasm->*load)(result.gp(), actual_addr, al);
1075 op(lasm, temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1076 (lasm->*store)(store_result, temp, actual_addr, al);
1077 __ cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
1078 __ b(ne, &retry);
1079 __ dmb(ISH);
1080}

1111
1112inline void AtomicBinop32(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Register dst_addr,
1113 Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1114 LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result,
1115 StoreType type,
1116 void (*op)(LiftoffAssembler*, Register, Register,
1117 Register)) {
1118 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value, result};
1119 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
1120 switch (type.value()) {
1121 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1122 __ LoadConstant(result.high(), WasmValue(0));
1123 result = result.low();
1124 value = value.low();
1125 [[fallthrough]];
1126 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1127 liftoff::AtomicOp32(lasm, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, value, result,
1128 pinned, &Assembler::ldrexb, &Assembler::strexb, op);
1129 return;
1130 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1131 __ LoadConstant(result.high(), WasmValue(0));
1132 result = result.low();
1133 value = value.low();
1134 [[fallthrough]];
1135 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1136 liftoff::AtomicOp32(lasm, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, value, result,
1137 pinned, &Assembler::ldrexh, &Assembler::strexh, op);
1138 return;
1139 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1140 __ LoadConstant(result.high(), WasmValue(0));
1141 result = result.low();
1142 value = value.low();
1143 [[fallthrough]];
1144 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1145 liftoff::AtomicOp32(lasm, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, value, result,
1146 pinned, &Assembler::ldrex, &Assembler::strex, op);
1147 return;
1148 default:
1149 UNREACHABLE();
1150 }
1151}
1152
1153inline void AtomicOp64(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Register dst_addr,
1154 Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1155 LiftoffRegister value,
1156 std::optional<LiftoffRegister> result,
1157 void (*op)(LiftoffAssembler*, LiftoffRegister,
1158 LiftoffRegister, LiftoffRegister)) {
1159 // strexd loads a 64 bit word into two registers. The first register needs
1160 // to have an even index, e.g. r8, the second register needs to be the one
1161 // with the next higher index, e.g. r9 if the first register is r8. In the
1162 // following code we use the fixed register pair r8/r9 to make the code here
1163 // simpler, even though other register pairs would also be possible.
1164 constexpr Register dst_low = r8;
1165 constexpr Register dst_high = r9;
1166
1167 // Make sure {dst_low} and {dst_high} are not occupied by any other value.
1168 Register value_low = value.low_gp();
1169 Register value_high = value.high_gp();
1170 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_low, dst_high};
1171 auto regs_to_check = {&dst_addr, &offset_reg, &value_low, &value_high};
1172 auto re_pin = [regs_to_check, &pinned] {
1173 for (auto* reg : regs_to_check) {
1174 if (*reg != no_reg) pinned.set(*reg);
1175 }
1176 };
1177 re_pin();
1178 __ ClearRegister(dst_low, regs_to_check, pinned);
1179 re_pin();
1180 __ ClearRegister(dst_high, regs_to_check, pinned);
1181 re_pin();
1182
1183 // Make sure that {result}, if it exists, also does not overlap with
1184 // {dst_low} and {dst_high}. We don't have to transfer the value stored in
1185 // {result}.
1186 Register result_low = no_reg;
1187 Register result_high = no_reg;
1188 if (result.has_value()) {
1189 result_low = result.value().low_gp();
1190 if (pinned.has(result_low)) {
1191 result_low = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1192 }
1193 pinned.set(result_low);
1194
1195 result_high = result.value().high_gp();
1196 if (pinned.has(result_high)) {
1197 result_high = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1198 }
1199 pinned.set(result_high);
1200 }
1201
1202 Register store_result = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1203
1204 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
1205 Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1206 lasm, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1207
1208 __ dmb(ISH);
1209 Label retry;
1210 __ bind(&retry);
1211 // {ldrexd} is needed here so that the {strexd} instruction below can
1212 // succeed. We don't need the value we are reading. We use {dst_low} and
1213 // {dst_high} as the destination registers because {ldrexd} has the same
1214 // restrictions on registers as {strexd}, see the comment above.
1215 __ ldrexd(dst_low, dst_high, actual_addr);
1216 if (result.has_value()) {
1217 __ mov(result_low, dst_low);
1218 __ mov(result_high, dst_high);
1219 }
1220 op(lasm, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_low, dst_high),
1221 LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_low, dst_high),
1222 LiftoffRegister::ForPair(value_low, value_high));
1223 __ strexd(store_result, dst_low, dst_high, actual_addr);
1224 __ cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
1225 __ b(ne, &retry);
1226 __ dmb(ISH);
1227
1228 if (result.has_value()) {
1229 if (result_low != result.value().low_gp()) {
1230 __ mov(result.value().low_gp(), result_low);
1231 }
1232 if (result_high != result.value().high_gp()) {
1233 __ mov(result.value().high_gp(), result_high);
1234 }
1235 }
1236}
1237
1238inline void I64Store(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, LiftoffRegister dst,
1239 LiftoffRegister, LiftoffRegister src) {
1240 __ mov(dst.low_gp(), src.low_gp());
1241 __ mov(dst.high_gp(), src.high_gp());
1242}
1243
1244#undef __
1245} // namespace liftoff
1246
1247void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
1248 Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1249 LoadType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
1250 bool /* i64_offset */) {
1251 if (type.value() != LoadType::kI64Load) {
1252 Load(dst, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, type, nullptr, true);
1253 dmb(ISH);
1254 return;
1255 }
1256 // ldrexd loads a 64 bit word into two registers. The first register needs to
1257 // have an even index, e.g. r8, the second register needs to be the one with
1258 // the next higher index, e.g. r9 if the first register is r8. In the
1259 // following code we use the fixed register pair r8/r9 to make the code here
1260 // simpler, even though other register pairs would also be possible.
1261 constexpr Register dst_low = r8;
1262 constexpr Register dst_high = r9;
1263 SpillRegisters(dst_low, dst_high);
1264 {
1265 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1266 Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1267 this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1268 ldrexd(dst_low, dst_high, actual_addr);
1269 dmb(ISH);
1270 }
1271
1272 ParallelRegisterMove(
1273 {{dst, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_low, dst_high), kI64}});
1274}
1275
1276void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStore(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
1277 uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
1278 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
1279 bool /* i64_offset */) {
1280 if (type.value() == StoreType::kI64Store) {
1281 liftoff::AtomicOp64(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, src, {},
1282 liftoff::I64Store);
1283 return;
1284 }
1285
1286 dmb(ISH);
1287 Store(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, src, type, pinned, nullptr, true);
1288 dmb(ISH);
1289 return;
1290}

1371namespace liftoff {
1372#define __ lasm->
1373
1374inline void AtomicI64CompareExchange(LiftoffAssembler* lasm,
1375 Register dst_addr_reg, Register offset_reg,
1376 uint32_t offset_imm,
1377 LiftoffRegister expected,
1378 LiftoffRegister new_value,
1379 LiftoffRegister result) {
1380 // To implement I64AtomicCompareExchange, we nearly need all registers, with
1381 // some registers having special constraints, e.g. like for {new_value} and
1382 // {result} the low-word register has to have an even register code, and the
1383 // high-word has to be in the next higher register. To avoid complicated
1384 // register allocation code here, we just assign fixed registers to all
1385 // values here, and then move all values into the correct register.
1386 Register dst_addr = r0;
1387 Register offset = r1;
1388 Register result_low = r4;
1389 Register result_high = r5;
1390 Register new_value_low = r2;
1391 Register new_value_high = r3;
1392 Register store_result = r6;
1393 Register expected_low = r8;
1394 Register expected_high = r9;
1395
1396 // We spill all registers, so that we can re-assign them afterwards.
1397 __ SpillRegisters(dst_addr, offset, result_low, result_high, new_value_low,
1398 new_value_high, store_result, expected_low, expected_high);
1399
1400 __ ParallelRegisterMove(
1401 {{LiftoffRegister::ForPair(new_value_low, new_value_high), new_value,
1402 kI64},
1403 {LiftoffRegister::ForPair(expected_low, expected_high), expected, kI64},
1404 {dst_addr, dst_addr_reg, kI32},
1405 {offset, offset_reg != no_reg ? offset_reg : offset, kI32}});
1406
1407 {
1408 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
1409 [[maybe_unused]] Register temp = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1410 lasm, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg == no_reg ? no_reg : offset,
1411 offset_imm, dst_addr);
1412 // Make sure the actual address is stored in the right register.
1413 DCHECK_EQ(dst_addr, temp);
1414 }
1415
1416 Label retry;
1417 Label done;
1418 __ dmb(ISH);
1419 __ bind(&retry);
1420 __ ldrexd(result_low, result_high, dst_addr);
1421 __ cmp(result_low, expected_low);
1422 __ b(ne, &done);
1423 __ cmp(result_high, expected_high);
1424 __ b(ne, &done);
1425 __ strexd(store_result, new_value_low, new_value_high, dst_addr);
1426 __ cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
1427 __ b(ne, &retry);
1428 __ dmb(ISH);
1429 __ bind(&done);
1430
1431 __ ParallelRegisterMove(
1432 {{result, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(result_low, result_high), kI64}});
1433}
1434#undef __
1435} // namespace liftoff
1436
1437void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicCompareExchange(
1438 Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1439 LiftoffRegister expected, LiftoffRegister new_value, LiftoffRegister result,
1440 StoreType type, bool /* i64_offset */) {
1441 if (type.value() == StoreType::kI64Store) {
1442 liftoff::AtomicI64CompareExchange(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
1443 expected, new_value, result);
1444 return;
1445 }
1446
1447 // The other versions of CompareExchange can share code, but need special load
1448 // and store instructions.
1449 void (Assembler::*load)(Register, Register, Condition) = nullptr;
1450 void (Assembler::*store)(Register, Register, Register, Condition) = nullptr;
1451
1452 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr};
1453 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
1454 // We need to remember the high word of {result}, so we can set it to zero in
1455 // the end if necessary.
1456 Register result_high = no_reg;
1457 switch (type.value()) {
1458 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1459 result_high = result.high_gp();
1460 result = result.low();
1461 new_value = new_value.low();
1462 expected = expected.low();
1463 [[fallthrough]];
1464 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1465 load = &Assembler::ldrexb;
1466 store = &Assembler::strexb;
1467 // We have to clear the high bits of {expected}, as we can only do a
1468 // 32-bit comparison. If the {expected} register is used, we spill it
1469 // first.
1470 if (cache_state()->is_used(expected)) {
1471 SpillRegister(expected);
1472 }
1473 uxtb(expected.gp(), expected.gp());
1474 break;
1475 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1476 result_high = result.high_gp();
1477 result = result.low();
1478 new_value = new_value.low();
1479 expected = expected.low();
1480 [[fallthrough]];
1481 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1482 load = &Assembler::ldrexh;
1483 store = &Assembler::strexh;
1484 // We have to clear the high bits of {expected}, as we can only do a
1485 // 32-bit comparison. If the {expected} register is used, we spill it
1486 // first.
1487 if (cache_state()->is_used(expected)) {
1488 SpillRegister(expected);
1489 }
1490 uxth(expected.gp(), expected.gp());
1491 break;
1492 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1493 result_high = result.high_gp();
1494 result = result.low();
1495 new_value = new_value.low();
1496 expected = expected.low();
1497 [[fallthrough]];
1498 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1499 load = &Assembler::ldrex;
1500 store = &Assembler::strex;
1501 break;
1502 default:
1503 UNREACHABLE();
1504 }
1505 pinned.set(new_value);
1506 pinned.set(expected);
1507
1508 Register result_reg = result.gp();
1509 if (pinned.has(result)) {
1510 result_reg = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1511 }
1512 pinned.set(LiftoffRegister(result));
1513 Register store_result = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1514
1515 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1516 Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1517 this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1518
1519 Label retry;
1520 Label done;
1521 dmb(ISH);
1522 bind(&retry);
1523 (this->*load)(result.gp(), actual_addr, al);
1524 cmp(result.gp(), expected.gp());
1525 b(ne, &done);
1526 (this->*store)(store_result, new_value.gp(), actual_addr, al);
1527 cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
1528 b(ne, &retry);
1529 dmb(ISH);
1530 bind(&done);
1531
1532 if (result.gp() != result_reg) {
1533 mov(result.gp(), result_reg);
1534 }
1535 if (result_high != no_reg) {
1536 LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(result_high), WasmValue(0));
1537 }
1538}

1562
1563void LiftoffAssembler::MoveStackValue(uint32_t dst_offset, uint32_t src_offset,
1564 ValueKind kind) {
1565 DCHECK_NE(dst_offset, src_offset);
1566 liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters temps{this};
1567 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1568 const int kRegSize = 4;
1569 DCHECK_EQ(0, SlotSizeForType(kind) % kRegSize);
1570 int words = SlotSizeForType(kind) / kRegSize;
1571 if (src_offset < dst_offset) {
1572 do {
1573 ldr(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset));
1574 str(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1575 dst_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
1576 src_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
1577 } while (--words);
1578 } else {
1579 while (words--) {
1580 ldr(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset - words * kRegSize));
1581 str(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset - words * kRegSize));
1582 }
1583 }
1584}
1585
1586void LiftoffAssembler::Move(Register dst, Register src, ValueKind kind) {
1587 DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1588 DCHECK(kind == kI32 || is_reference(kind));
1589 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, src);
1590}
1591
1592void LiftoffAssembler::Move(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister src,
1593 ValueKind kind) {
1594 DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1595 if (kind == kF32) {
1596 vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src));
1597 } else if (kind == kF64) {
1598 vmov(dst, src);
1599 } else {
1600 DCHECK_EQ(kS128, kind);
1601 vmov(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src));
1602 }
1603}
1604
1605void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
1606 // The {str} instruction needs a temp register when the immediate in the
1607 // provided MemOperand does not fit into 12 bits. This happens for large stack
1608 // frames. This DCHECK checks that the temp register is available when needed.
1609 DCHECK(UseScratchRegisterScope{this}.CanAcquire());
1610 DCHECK_LT(0, offset);
1611 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1612 MemOperand dst(fp, -offset);
1613 liftoff::Store(this, reg, dst, kind);
1614}
1615
1616void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1617 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1618 MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1619 UseScratchRegisterScope assembler_temps(this);
1620 liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters liftoff_temps{this};
1621 Register src = no_reg;
1622 // The scratch register will be required by str if multiple instructions
1623 // are required to encode the offset, and so we cannot use it in that case.
1624 if (!ImmediateFitsAddrMode2Instruction(dst.offset())) {
1625 src = liftoff_temps.Acquire();
1626 } else {
1627 src = assembler_temps.Acquire();
1628 }
1629 switch (value.type().kind()) {
1630 case kI32:
1631 mov(src, Operand(value.to_i32()));
1632 str(src, dst);
1633 break;
1634 case kI64: {
1635 int32_t low_word = value.to_i64();
1636 mov(src, Operand(low_word));
1637 str(src, liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kLowWord));
1638 int32_t high_word = value.to_i64() >> 32;
1639 mov(src, Operand(high_word));
1640 str(src, liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kHighWord));
1641 break;
1642 }
1643 default:
1644 // We do not track f32 and f64 constants, hence they are unreachable.
1645 UNREACHABLE();
1646 }
1647}
1648
1649void LiftoffAssembler::Fill(LiftoffRegister reg, int offset, ValueKind kind) {
1650 liftoff::Load(this, reg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset), kind);
1651}
1652
1653void LiftoffAssembler::FillI64Half(Register reg, int offset, RegPairHalf half) {
1654 ldr(reg, liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, half));
1655}
1656
1657void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1658 DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1659 DCHECK_EQ(0, size % 4);
1660 RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1661
1662 // We need a zero reg. Always use r0 for that, and push it before to restore
1663 // its value afterwards.
1664 push(r0);
1665 mov(r0, Operand(0));
1666
1667 if (size <= 36) {
1668 // Special straight-line code for up to 9 words. Generates one
1669 // instruction per word.
1670 for (int offset = 4; offset <= size; offset += 4) {
1671 str(r0, liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(start + offset, kLowWord));
1672 }
1673 } else {
1674 // General case for bigger counts (9 instructions).
1675 // Use r1 for start address (inclusive), r2 for end address (exclusive).
1676 push(r1);
1677 push(r2);
1678 sub(r1, fp, Operand(start + size));
1679 sub(r2, fp, Operand(start));
1680
1681 Label loop;
1682 bind(&loop);
1683 str(r0, MemOperand(r1, /* offset */ kSystemPointerSize, PostIndex));
1684 cmp(r1, r2);
1685 b(&loop, ne);
1686
1687 pop(r2);
1688 pop(r1);
1689 }
1690
1691 pop(r0);
1692}

1694void LiftoffAssembler::LoadSpillAddress(Register dst, int offset,
1695 ValueKind /* kind */) {
1696 sub(dst, fp, Operand(offset));
1697}

1771void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_sari(Register dst, Register src,
1772 int32_t amount) {
1773 if (V8_LIKELY((amount & 31) != 0)) {
1774 asr(dst, src, Operand(amount & 31));
1775 } else if (dst != src) {
1776 mov(dst, src);
1777 }
1778}

1780void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shr(Register dst, Register src,
1781 Register amount) {
1782 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1783 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1784 and_(scratch, amount, Operand(0x1f));
1785 lsr(dst, src, Operand(scratch));
1786}
1787void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shri(Register dst, Register src,
1788 int32_t amount) {
1789 if (V8_LIKELY((amount & 31) != 0)) {
1790 lsr(dst, src, Operand(amount & 31));
1791 } else if (dst != src) {
1792 mov(dst, src);
1793 }
1794}

1873namespace liftoff {
1874inline void GeneratePopCnt(Assembler* assm, Register dst, Register src,
1875 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
1876 DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst, scratch1, scratch2));
1877 if (src == scratch1) std::swap(scratch1, scratch2);
1878 // x = x - ((x & (0x55555555 << 1)) >> 1)
1879 assm->and_(scratch1, src, Operand(0xaaaaaaaa));
1880 assm->sub(dst, src, Operand(scratch1, LSR, 1));
1881 // x = (x & 0x33333333) + ((x & (0x33333333 << 2)) >> 2)
1882 assm->mov(scratch1, Operand(0x33333333));
1883 assm->and_(scratch2, dst, Operand(scratch1, LSL, 2));
1884 assm->and_(scratch1, dst, scratch1);
1885 assm->add(dst, scratch1, Operand(scratch2, LSR, 2));
1886 // x = (x + (x >> 4)) & 0x0F0F0F0F
1887 assm->add(dst, dst, Operand(dst, LSR, 4));
1888 assm->and_(dst, dst, Operand(0x0f0f0f0f));
1889 // x = x + (x >> 8)
1890 assm->add(dst, dst, Operand(dst, LSR, 8));
1891 // x = x + (x >> 16)
1892 assm->add(dst, dst, Operand(dst, LSR, 16));
1893 // x = x & 0x3F
1894 assm->and_(dst, dst, Operand(0x3f));
1895}
1896} // namespace liftoff

1898bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_popcnt(Register dst, Register src) {
1899 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
1900 Register scratch1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1901 Register scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1902 liftoff::GeneratePopCnt(this, dst, src, scratch1, scratch2);
1903 return true;
1904}
1905
1906void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divs(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1907 Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1908 Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1909 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
1910 bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "i32_divs");
1911 return;
1912 }
1913 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SUDIV);
1914 // Issue division early so we can perform the trapping checks whilst it
1915 // completes.
1916 bool speculative_sdiv = dst != lhs && dst != rhs;
1917 if (speculative_sdiv) {
1918 sdiv(dst, lhs, rhs);
1919 }
1920 Label noTrap;
1921 // Check for division by zero.
1922 cmp(rhs, Operand(0));
1923 b(trap_div_by_zero, eq);
1924 // Check for kMinInt / -1. This is unrepresentable.
1925 cmp(rhs, Operand(-1));
1926 b(&noTrap, ne);
1927 cmp(lhs, Operand(kMinInt));
1928 b(trap_div_unrepresentable, eq);
1929 bind(&noTrap);
1930 if (!speculative_sdiv) {
1931 sdiv(dst, lhs, rhs);
1932 }
1933}
1934
1935void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1936 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1937 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
1938 bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "i32_divu");
1939 return;
1940 }
1941 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SUDIV);
1942 // Check for division by zero.
1943 cmp(rhs, Operand(0));
1944 b(trap_div_by_zero, eq);
1945 udiv(dst, lhs, rhs);
1946}
1947
1948void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_rems(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1949 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1950 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
1951 // When this case is handled, a check for ARMv7 is required to use mls.
1952 // Mls support is implied with SUDIV support.
1953 bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "i32_rems");
1954 return;
1955 }
1956 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SUDIV);
1957 // No need to check kMinInt / -1 because the result is kMinInt and then
1958 // kMinInt * -1 -> kMinInt. In this case, the Msub result is therefore 0.
1959 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1960 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1961 sdiv(scratch, lhs, rhs);
1962 // Check for division by zero.
1963 cmp(rhs, Operand(0));
1964 b(trap_div_by_zero, eq);
1965 // Compute remainder.
1966 mls(dst, scratch, rhs, lhs);
1967}
1968
1969void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_remu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1970 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1971 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
1972 // When this case is handled, a check for ARMv7 is required to use mls.
1973 // Mls support is implied with SUDIV support.
1974 bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "i32_remu");
1975 return;
1976 }
1977 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SUDIV);
1978 // No need to check kMinInt / -1 because the result is kMinInt and then
1979 // kMinInt * -1 -> kMinInt. In this case, the Msub result is therefore 0.
1980 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1981 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1982 udiv(scratch, lhs, rhs);
1983 // Check for division by zero.
1984 cmp(rhs, Operand(0));
1985 b(trap_div_by_zero, eq);
1986 // Compute remainder.
1987 mls(dst, scratch, rhs, lhs);
1988}

2005void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_mul(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2006 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2007 // Idea:
2008 // [ lhs_hi | lhs_lo ] * [ rhs_hi | rhs_lo ]
2009 // = [ lhs_hi * rhs_lo | ] (32 bit mul, shift 32)
2010 // + [ lhs_lo * rhs_hi | ] (32 bit mul, shift 32)
2011 // + [ lhs_lo * rhs_lo ] (32x32->64 mul, shift 0)
2012 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2013 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2014 // scratch = lhs_hi * rhs_lo
2015 mul(scratch, lhs.high_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
2016 // scratch += lhs_lo * rhs_hi
2017 mla(scratch, lhs.low_gp(), rhs.high_gp(), scratch);
2018 // TODO(arm): use umlal once implemented correctly in the simulator.
2019 // [dst_hi|dst_lo] = lhs_lo * rhs_lo
2020 umull(dst.low_gp(), dst.high_gp(), lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
2021 // dst_hi += scratch
2022 add(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp(), scratch);
2023}

2095void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_clz(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2096 // return high == 0 ? 32 + CLZ32(low) : CLZ32(high);
2097 Label done;
2098 Label high_is_zero;
2099 cmp(src.high_gp(), Operand(0));
2100 b(&high_is_zero, eq);
2101
2102 clz(dst.low_gp(), src.high_gp());
2103 jmp(&done);
2104
2105 bind(&high_is_zero);
2106 clz(dst.low_gp(), src.low_gp());
2107 add(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(32));
2108
2109 bind(&done);
2110 mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0)); // High word of result is always 0.
2111}
2112
2113void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_ctz(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2114 // return low == 0 ? 32 + CTZ32(high) : CTZ32(low);
2115 // CTZ32(x) = CLZ(RBIT(x))
2116 Label done;
2117 Label low_is_zero;
2118 cmp(src.low_gp(), Operand(0));
2119 b(&low_is_zero, eq);
2120
2121 rbit(dst.low_gp(), src.low_gp());
2122 clz(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp());
2123 jmp(&done);
2124
2125 bind(&low_is_zero);
2126 rbit(dst.low_gp(), src.high_gp());
2127 clz(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp());
2128 add(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(32));
2129
2130 bind(&done);
2131 mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0)); // High word of result is always 0.
2132}
2133
2134bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_popcnt(LiftoffRegister dst,
2135 LiftoffRegister src) {
2136 // Produce partial popcnts in the two dst registers, making sure not to
2137 // overwrite the second src register before using it.
2138 Register src1 = src.high_gp() == dst.low_gp() ? src.high_gp() : src.low_gp();
2139 Register src2 = src.high_gp() == dst.low_gp() ? src.low_gp() : src.high_gp();
2140 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst, src2};
2141 Register scratch1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
2142 Register scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2143 liftoff::GeneratePopCnt(this, dst.low_gp(), src1, scratch1, scratch2);
2144 liftoff::GeneratePopCnt(this, dst.high_gp(), src2, scratch1, scratch2);
2145 // Now add the two into the lower dst reg and clear the higher dst reg.
2146 add(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp(), dst.high_gp());
2147 mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
2148 return true;
2149}
2150
2151void LiftoffAssembler::IncrementSmi(LiftoffRegister dst, int offset) {
2152 if (!is_int12(offset)) {
2153 // For large offsets, ldr/str will need a scratch register, but we need
2154 // the single available scratch register here. So fold the offset into the
2155 // base address.
2156 // Note: if we ever want to use this function for callers that don't want
2157 // {dst} to get clobbered, we could spill it to the stack and restore it
2158 // later.
2159 add(dst.gp(), dst.gp(), Operand(offset));
2160 offset = 0;
2161 }
2162 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2163 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2164 ldr(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
2165 add(scratch, scratch, Operand(Smi::FromInt(1)));
2166 str(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
2167}

2266
2267void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2268 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2269 constexpr uint32_t kF32SignBit = uint32_t{1} << 31;
2270 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2271 Register scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
2272 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
2273 VmovLow(scratch, lhs);
2274 // Clear sign bit in {scratch}.
2275 bic(scratch, scratch, Operand(kF32SignBit));
2276 VmovLow(scratch2, rhs);
2277 // Isolate sign bit in {scratch2}.
2278 and_(scratch2, scratch2, Operand(kF32SignBit));
2279 // Combine {scratch2} into {scratch}.
2280 orr(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
2281 VmovLow(dst, scratch);
2282}
2283
2284void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2285 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2286 constexpr uint32_t kF64SignBitHighWord = uint32_t{1} << 31;
2287 // On arm, we cannot hold the whole f64 value in a gp register, so we just
2288 // operate on the upper half (UH).
2289 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2290 Register scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
2291 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
2292 VmovHigh(scratch, lhs);
2293 // Clear sign bit in {scratch}.
2294 bic(scratch, scratch, Operand(kF64SignBitHighWord));
2295 VmovHigh(scratch2, rhs);
2296 // Isolate sign bit in {scratch2}.
2297 and_(scratch2, scratch2, Operand(kF64SignBitHighWord));
2298 // Combine {scratch2} into {scratch}.
2299 orr(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
2300 vmov(dst, lhs);
2301 VmovHigh(dst, scratch);
2302}
2303
2304bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
2305 LiftoffRegister dst,
2306 LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
2307 switch (opcode) {
2308 case kExprI32ConvertI64:
2309 MacroAssembler::Move(dst.gp(), src.low_gp());
2310 return true;
2311 case kExprI32SConvertF32: {
2312 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2313 SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2314 vcvt_s32_f32(
2315 scratch_f,
2316 liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp())); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
2317 vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2318 // Check underflow and NaN.
2319 vmov(scratch_f, Float32(static_cast<float>(INT32_MIN)));
2320 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()), scratch_f);
2321 b(trap, lt);
2322 // Check overflow.
2323 cmp(dst.gp(), Operand(-1));
2324 b(trap, vs);
2325 return true;
2326 }
2327 case kExprI32UConvertF32: {
2328 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2329 SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2330 vcvt_u32_f32(
2331 scratch_f,
2332 liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp())); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
2333 vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2334 // Check underflow and NaN.
2335 vmov(scratch_f, Float32(-1.0f));
2336 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()), scratch_f);
2337 b(trap, le);
2338 // Check overflow.
2339 cmp(dst.gp(), Operand(-1));
2340 b(trap, eq);
2341 return true;
2342 }
2343 case kExprI32SConvertF64: {
2344 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2345 SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2346 vcvt_s32_f64(scratch_f, src.fp()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
2347 vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2348 // Check underflow and NaN.
2349 DwVfpRegister scratch_d = temps.AcquireD();
2350 vmov(scratch_d, base::Double(static_cast<double>(INT32_MIN - 1.0)));
2351 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(src.fp(), scratch_d);
2352 b(trap, le);
2353 // Check overflow.
2354 vmov(scratch_d, base::Double(static_cast<double>(INT32_MAX + 1.0)));
2355 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(src.fp(), scratch_d);
2356 b(trap, ge);
2357 return true;
2358 }
2359 case kExprI32UConvertF64: {
2360 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2361 SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2362 vcvt_u32_f64(scratch_f, src.fp()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
2363 vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2364 // Check underflow and NaN.
2365 DwVfpRegister scratch_d = temps.AcquireD();
2366 vmov(scratch_d, base::Double(static_cast<double>(-1.0)));
2367 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(src.fp(), scratch_d);
2368 b(trap, le);
2369 // Check overflow.
2370 vmov(scratch_d, base::Double(static_cast<double>(UINT32_MAX + 1.0)));
2371 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(src.fp(), scratch_d);
2372 b(trap, ge);
2373 return true;
2374 }
2375 case kExprI32SConvertSatF32: {
2376 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2377 SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2378 vcvt_s32_f32(
2379 scratch_f,
2380 liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp())); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
2381 vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2382 return true;
2383 }
2384 case kExprI32UConvertSatF32: {
2385 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2386 SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2387 vcvt_u32_f32(
2388 scratch_f,
2389 liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp())); // f32 -> u32 round to zero.
2390 vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2391 return true;
2392 }
2393 case kExprI32SConvertSatF64: {
2394 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2395 SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2396 vcvt_s32_f64(scratch_f, src.fp()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
2397 vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2398 return true;
2399 }
2400 case kExprI32UConvertSatF64: {
2401 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2402 SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2403 vcvt_u32_f64(scratch_f, src.fp()); // f64 -> u32 round to zero.
2404 vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2405 return true;
2406 }
2407 case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
2408 vmov(dst.gp(), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()));
2409 return true;
2410 case kExprI64SConvertI32:
2411 if (dst.low_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), src.gp());
2412 mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(src.gp(), ASR, 31));
2413 return true;
2414 case kExprI64UConvertI32:
2415 if (dst.low_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), src.gp());
2416 mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
2417 return true;
2418 case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
2419 vmov(dst.low_gp(), dst.high_gp(), src.fp());
2420 return true;
2421 case kExprF32SConvertI32: {
2422 SwVfpRegister dst_float = liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp());
2423 vmov(dst_float, src.gp());
2424 vcvt_f32_s32(dst_float, dst_float);
2425 return true;
2426 }
2427 case kExprF32UConvertI32: {
2428 SwVfpRegister dst_float = liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp());
2429 vmov(dst_float, src.gp());
2430 vcvt_f32_u32(dst_float, dst_float);
2431 return true;
2432 }
2433 case kExprF32ConvertF64:
2434 vcvt_f32_f64(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src.fp());
2435 return true;
2436 case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
2437 vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src.gp());
2438 return true;
2439 case kExprF64SConvertI32: {
2440 vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src.gp());
2441 vcvt_f64_s32(dst.fp(), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()));
2442 return true;
2443 }
2444 case kExprF64UConvertI32: {
2445 vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src.gp());
2446 vcvt_f64_u32(dst.fp(), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()));
2447 return true;
2448 }
2449 case kExprF64ConvertF32:
2450 vcvt_f64_f32(dst.fp(), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()));
2451 return true;
2452 case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
2453 vmov(dst.fp(), src.low_gp(), src.high_gp());
2454 return true;
2455 case kExprF64SConvertI64:
2456 case kExprF64UConvertI64:
2457 case kExprI64SConvertF32:
2458 case kExprI64UConvertF32:
2459 case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
2460 case kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
2461 case kExprF32SConvertI64:
2462 case kExprF32UConvertI64:
2463 case kExprI64SConvertF64:
2464 case kExprI64UConvertF64:
2465 case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
2466 case kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
2467 // These cases can be handled by the C fallback function.
2468 return false;
2469 default:
2470 UNREACHABLE();
2471 }
2472}

2500void LiftoffAssembler::emit_jump(Label* label) { b(label); }

2503
2504void LiftoffAssembler::emit_cond_jump(Condition cond, Label* label,
2505 ValueKind kind, Register lhs,
2506 Register rhs,
2507 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2508 if (rhs == no_reg) {
2509 DCHECK_EQ(kind, kI32);
2510 cmp(lhs, Operand(0));
2511 } else {
2512 DCHECK(kind == kI32 ||
2513 (is_reference(kind) && (cond == kEqual || cond == kNotEqual)));
2514 cmp(lhs, rhs);
2515 }
2516 b(label, cond);
2517}

2519void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_cond_jumpi(Condition cond, Label* label,
2520 Register lhs, int32_t imm,
2521 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2522 cmp(lhs, Operand(imm));
2523 b(label, cond);
2524}

2532 Register lhs, Register rhs) {
2533 cmp(lhs, rhs);

2535 mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, cond);
2536}

2539 orr(dst, src.low_gp(), src.high_gp());
2540 clz(dst, dst);
2541 mov(dst, Operand(dst, LSR, 5));
2542}
2543
2544void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2545 LiftoffRegister lhs,
2546 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2547 // For signed i64 comparisons, we still need to use unsigned comparison for
2548 // the low word (the only bit carrying signedness information is the MSB in
2549 // the high word).
2550 Condition unsigned_cond = liftoff::MakeUnsigned(cond);
2551 Label set_cond;
2552 Label cont;
2553 LiftoffRegister dest = LiftoffRegister(dst);
2554 bool speculative_move = !dest.overlaps(lhs) && !dest.overlaps(rhs);
2555 if (speculative_move) {
2556 mov(dst, Operand(0));
2557 }
2558 // Compare high word first. If it differs, use it for the set_cond. If it's
2559 // equal, compare the low word and use that for set_cond.
2560 cmp(lhs.high_gp(), rhs.high_gp());
2561 if (unsigned_cond == cond) {
2562 cmp(lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp(), eq);
2563 if (!speculative_move) {
2564 mov(dst, Operand(0));
2565 }
2566 mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, cond);
2567 } else {
2568 // If the condition predicate for the low differs from that for the high
2569 // word, the conditional move instructions must be separated.
2570 b(ne, &set_cond);
2571 cmp(lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
2572 if (!speculative_move) {
2573 mov(dst, Operand(0));
2574 }
2575 mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, unsigned_cond);
2576 b(&cont);
2577 bind(&set_cond);
2578 if (!speculative_move) {
2579 mov(dst, Operand(0));
2580 }
2581 mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, cond);
2582 bind(&cont);
2583 }
2584}
2585
2586void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2587 DoubleRegister lhs,
2588 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2589 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(lhs),
2590 liftoff::GetFloatRegister(rhs));
2591 mov(dst, Operand(0), LeaveCC);
2592 mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, cond);
2593 if (cond != ne) {
2594 // If V flag set, at least one of the arguments was a Nan -> false.
2595 mov(dst, Operand(0), LeaveCC, vs);
2596 }
2597}
2598
2599void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2600 DoubleRegister lhs,
2601 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2602 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(lhs, rhs);
2603 mov(dst, Operand(0), LeaveCC);
2604 mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, cond);
2605 if (cond != ne) {
2606 // If V flag set, at least one of the arguments was a Nan -> false.
2607 mov(dst, Operand(0), LeaveCC, vs);
2608 }
2609}

2618void LiftoffAssembler::emit_smi_check(Register obj, Label* target,
2619 SmiCheckMode mode,
2620 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {

2626void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTransform(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
2627 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
2628 LoadType type,
2629 LoadTransformationKind transform,
2630 uint32_t* protected_load_pc) {
2631 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2632 Register actual_src_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
2633 this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
2634 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2635 MachineType memtype = type.mem_type();
2636
2637 if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
2638 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2639 vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2640 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2641 vmovl(NeonS8, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2642 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
2643 vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2644 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2645 vmovl(NeonU8, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2646 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2647 vld1(Neon16, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2648 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2649 vmovl(NeonS16, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2650 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
2651 vld1(Neon16, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2652 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2653 vmovl(NeonU16, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2654 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2655 vld1(Neon32, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2656 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2657 vmovl(NeonS32, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2658 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
2659 vld1(Neon32, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2660 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2661 vmovl(NeonU32, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2662 }
2663 } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend) {
2664 Simd128Register dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
2665 if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2666 vmov(dest, 0);
2667 vld1s(Neon32, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()), 0,
2668 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2669 } else {
2670 DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), memtype);
2671 vmov(dest.high(), 0);
2672 vld1(Neon64, NeonListOperand(dest.low()),
2673 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2674 }
2675 } else {
2676 DCHECK_EQ(LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, transform);
2677 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2678 vld1r(Neon8, NeonListOperand(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst)),
2679 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2680 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2681 vld1r(Neon16, NeonListOperand(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst)),
2682 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2683 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2684 vld1r(Neon32, NeonListOperand(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst)),
2685 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2686 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
2687 vld1(Neon32, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2688 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2689 MacroAssembler::Move(dst.high_fp(), dst.low_fp());
2690 }
2691 }
2692}
2693
2694void LiftoffAssembler::LoadLane(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
2695 Register addr, Register offset_reg,
2696 uintptr_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
2697 uint8_t laneidx, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2698 bool /* i64_offset */) {
2699 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2700 Register actual_src_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
2701 this, &temps, addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
2702 MacroAssembler::Move(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
2703 liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src));
2704 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2705 LoadStoreLaneParams load_params(type.mem_type().representation(), laneidx);
2706 NeonListOperand dst_op =
2707 NeonListOperand(load_params.low_op ? dst.low_fp() : dst.high_fp());
2708 MacroAssembler::LoadLane(load_params.sz, dst_op, load_params.laneidx,
2709 NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2710}
2711
2712void LiftoffAssembler::StoreLane(Register dst, Register offset,
2713 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
2714 StoreType type, uint8_t laneidx,
2715 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
2716 bool /* i64_offset */) {
2717 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2718 Register actual_dst_addr =
2719 liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(this, &temps, dst, offset, offset_imm);
2720 *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
2721
2722 LoadStoreLaneParams store_params(type.mem_rep(), laneidx);
2723 NeonListOperand src_op =
2724 NeonListOperand(store_params.low_op ? src.low_fp() : src.high_fp());
2725 MacroAssembler::StoreLane(store_params.sz, src_op, store_params.laneidx,
2726 NeonMemOperand(actual_dst_addr));
2727}

2729void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_swizzle(LiftoffRegister dst,
2730 LiftoffRegister lhs,
2731 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2732 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2733
2734 NeonListOperand table(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
2735 if (dst == lhs) {
2736 // dst will be overwritten, so keep the table somewhere else.
2737 QwNeonRegister tbl = temps.AcquireQ();
2738 MacroAssembler::Move(tbl, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
2739 table = NeonListOperand(tbl);
2740 }
2741
2742 vtbl(dst.low_fp(), table, rhs.low_fp());
2743 vtbl(dst.high_fp(), table, rhs.high_fp());
2744}

2917void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_pmin(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2918 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2919 QwNeonRegister dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
2920 QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
2921 QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
2922
2923 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(right.low(), left.low());
2924 if (dst != rhs) vmov(dest.low(), right.low(), mi);
2925 if (dst != lhs) vmov(dest.low(), left.low(), NegateCondition(mi));
2926 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(right.high(), left.high());
2927 if (dst != rhs) vmov(dest.high(), right.high(), mi);
2928 if (dst != lhs) vmov(dest.high(), left.high(), NegateCondition(mi));
2929}

2931void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_pmax(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2932 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2933 QwNeonRegister dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
2934 QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
2935 QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
2936
2937 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(right.low(), left.low());
2938 if (dst != rhs) vmov(dest.low(), right.low(), gt);
2939 if (dst != lhs) vmov(dest.low(), left.low(), NegateCondition(gt));
2940 VFPCompareAndSetFlags(right.high(), left.high());
2941 if (dst != rhs) vmov(dest.high(), right.high(), gt);
2942 if (dst != lhs) vmov(dest.high(), left.high(), NegateCondition(gt));
2943}
